<BODY LANG="en-US" LINK="#0000ff" VLINK="#800080" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="back.jpg" DIR="LTR">

<center>

			<P STYLE="border: none; padding: 0cm"><B>Loading a
			different map or set of cards</B></P>
			<P STYLE="border: none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: medium">
			Loading a different map<BR>
			</P>
			<P STYLE="border: none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: medium">
			Loading a different map only be done from the New Game screen,
			click on the Choose Map button and a smaller window should open,
			navigate to the map file and open it to load it. If the map file
			is valid, a mini picture should be displayed in the Map: window
			showing the map that you have selected, and the map file name will
			be displayed.</P>
			<P STYLE="border: none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: medium">
			Valid maps supplied are:</P>


	<P STYLE="border: none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: medium">
	<b>board.map</b> (default map)</P>

	<P STYLE="border: none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: medium">
	<b>aa.map</b> (Axis and Allies Map)</P>

	<P STYLE="border: medium none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: 700">
	luca.map<span style="font-weight: 400"> (map made by Luca)</span></P>

	<P STYLE="border: medium none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: 700">
	risk.map<span style="font-weight: 400"> (map from a old risk game)</span></P>

	<P STYLE="border: medium none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: 700">
	risk2.map<span style="font-weight: 400"> (map from the game RiskII)</span></P>

	<P STYLE="border: medium none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: 700">
	risk2210.map<span style="font-weight: 400"> (map from the game Risk 2210)</span></P>

	<P STYLE="border: medium none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: 700">
	<b>sersom.map</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> (supplied map)</span></P>

	<P STYLE="border: medium none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: 700">
	roman_empire.map<span style="font-weight: 400"> (roman empire map)</span></P>

	<P STYLE="border: none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: medium">
	<b>teg.map</b> (map from the game TEG)</P>

	<P STYLE="border: none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: medium">
	<b>tube.map</b> (map of London Zone 1 Tube)</P>

	<P STYLE="border: none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: medium">
	<b>uk.map</b> (alternative map requirement)</P>

	<P STYLE="border: none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: medium">
	<b>world.map</b> (geographical map of the world)</P>

			<P STYLE="border: none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: medium">
			If the map is not valid, then the mini map will remain as it was,
			i.e. no change.<BR>
			</P>
			<P STYLE="border: none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: medium">
			Loading a new set of cards</P>
			<P STYLE="border: none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: medium">
			Valid cards supplied are:</P>

<P STYLE="border: none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: medium">
<b>nomission.cards</b> (cards for uk.map, tube.map and others)</P>

<P STYLE="border: medium none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: 700">
risk.cards<span style="font-weight: 400"> (these are the standard cards)</span></P>

<P STYLE="border: medium none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: 700">
risk2210.cards<span style="font-weight: 400"> (cards that are used with risk2210.map)</span></P>

<P STYLE="border: medium none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: 700">
roman_empire.cards<span style="font-weight: 400"> (cards that are used with roman_empire.map)</span></P>

			<P STYLE="border: none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: medium">
			Loading a set of cards can only be done form the New Game screen</P>
			<P STYLE="border: none; padding: 0cm; font-weight: medium">
			Loading a different map only be done from the New Game screen,
			click on the Choose Cards button and a smaller window should open,
			navigate to the cards file and open it to load it, it
			will be displayed in the cards field.</P>

	<p>To download more maps go <a target="_blank" href="http://jrisk.sf.net/getmaps.shtml">here</a>.</p>


</center>
</BODY>
</HTML>